What about his wife?

791
00:54:21,180 --> 00:54:23,060
I've been waiting
for that question.

792
00:54:25,010 --> 00:54:26,090
She was...

793
00:54:27,080 --> 00:54:29,090
wonderful, mad,

794
00:54:30,000 --> 00:54:32,900
sexy, bright.

795
00:54:34,030 --> 00:54:35,090
Were you close?

796
00:54:35,090 --> 00:54:36,190
We used to have this group,

797
00:54:36,190 --> 00:54:39,940
this elite group, we'd come here

798
00:54:39,940 --> 00:54:42,900
during our night shift
with our cell phones
and our beepers.

799
00:54:43,080 --> 00:54:46,910
We'd have discussions,
play fast games of chess,

800
00:54:46,910 --> 00:54:50,130
and then, Carol and Franz
would pop in...

801
00:54:51,070 --> 00:54:54,980
and he would get
very drunk, very fast.

802
00:54:55,900 --> 00:54:58,130
And she would play chess
with us.

803
00:54:59,150 --> 00:55:01,110
And win.

804
00:55:01,110 --> 00:55:04,010
Hey, she beat all of us
at one time or another.

805
00:55:08,020 --> 00:55:09,150
And then what happened?

806
00:55:11,980 --> 00:55:15,150
You know what,
you ask too many questions.

807
00:55:16,980 --> 00:55:19,030
You get the job,
you ask the questions.

808
00:55:23,190 --> 00:55:24,970
Well...

809
00:55:25,910 --> 00:55:27,170
Hey, there he is.

810
00:55:29,940 --> 00:55:32,140
Oh, wait, now. You don't look
as relaxed as I told you to be.

811
00:55:33,110 --> 00:55:34,950
He look relaxed to you?

812
00:55:36,110 --> 00:55:39,110
Phil, you need to help me.

813
00:55:40,100 --> 00:55:42,180
I need to get my book pulled.

814
00:55:45,010 --> 00:55:47,020
(sighs) Bill...

815
00:55:47,020 --> 00:55:51,070
The book is in every book store
and the half the supermarkets
across America.

816
00:55:52,060 --> 00:55:55,040
You can't pull a ship back
into port when it's going
the opposite way.

817
00:55:56,100 --> 00:55:58,970
It's the best opening title
this year. They're getting
incredible feedback.

818
00:56:00,030 --> 00:56:02,000
Tell him I'll sue.

819
00:56:04,960 --> 00:56:08,990
Well, have I ever been able to
stop you from doing
what you wanna do? Hmm?

820
00:56:09,910 --> 00:56:11,140
I'm sure they'll tell you
to go ahead.

821
00:56:11,140 --> 00:56:14,150
And I'm not an agent
or anything,
but you do have a contract.

822
00:56:14,150 --> 00:56:16,100
You wrote the thing,
and they spent
all kinds of money

823
00:56:16,100 --> 00:56:18,940
to print it, advertise it
and supply the retailers.

824
00:56:18,940 --> 00:56:20,130
So you can kick and scream
all you want,

825
00:56:20,130 --> 00:56:22,960
but you don't have a fucking leg
to stand on in the real world,

826
00:56:22,960 --> 00:56:24,090
and you know it!
And I can't help you.

827
00:56:29,160 --> 00:56:30,180
Phil...

828
00:56:32,100 --> 00:56:34,020
Can I talk to you for a second?

829
00:56:34,980 --> 00:56:36,000
What?

830
00:56:36,000 --> 00:56:37,130
You heard me.

831
00:56:44,080 --> 00:56:45,110
Phil...

832
00:56:46,950 --> 00:56:49,910
you're fired.
Put a spin on that.

833
00:56:55,950 --> 00:56:57,090
I hate writers.

834
00:57:04,140 --> 00:57:06,140
(traffic buzzing)

835
00:57:09,080 --> 00:57:10,140
(wheels rolling)

836
00:57:10,140 --> 00:57:12,080
(keyboard keys clacking)

837
00:57:13,170 --> 00:57:15,960
Okay, let's try it.

838
00:57:17,130 --> 00:57:20,940
[man] (distorted voice) You are
going to see how naive you are.

839
00:57:20,940 --> 00:57:23,090
Because it's gonna get
much harder to deal with

840
00:57:23,090 --> 00:57:25,920
when it's the girl.

841
00:57:25,920 --> 00:57:28,900
You'd hate to have her think
that you're a fool.

842
00:57:28,900 --> 00:57:30,010
You'd eat a yard of shit...

843
00:57:30,010 --> 00:57:32,040
It doesn't sound
any different to me.

844
00:57:33,010 --> 00:57:35,180
It sounds completely different.

845
00:57:35,180 --> 00:57:37,170
Help us here, son.
We're not trained,

846
00:57:37,170 --> 00:57:39,900
so we're not just quite hearing
what you're hearing.

847
00:57:39,900 --> 00:57:44,020
Right now, I've taken about half
the high-end multi-dupe
simul-masking out.

848
00:57:46,110 --> 00:57:48,140
(sighs) That means...

849
00:57:50,120 --> 00:57:54,030
A part of his voice
is pretty much right out there
for us to hear.

850
00:57:54,030 --> 00:57:56,120
Only it's still masked
by all the other garbage

851
00:57:56,120 --> 00:57:58,140
I've gotta take
from the rest of his voice.

852
00:58:00,950 --> 00:58:03,050
-(sighs)
-[Bill] Peter Palmer, please.

853
00:58:04,990 --> 00:58:08,170
Can you tell him to call me
as soon as he shows up?
It's his father.

854
00:58:09,170 --> 00:58:11,060
On the money, Moose.

855
00:58:12,070 --> 00:58:13,150
You found Franz.

856
00:58:13,150 --> 00:58:15,070
Just outside
lovely Bennington, Illinois.

857
00:58:15,070 --> 00:58:16,110
He lives with his son.

858
00:58:17,950 --> 00:58:19,090
(exhales sharply)

859
00:58:21,940 --> 00:58:23,930
Be careful, Hewlett.

860
00:58:25,140 --> 00:58:27,070
(sighs)

861
00:58:27,070 --> 00:58:30,070
(dramatic music playing)

862
00:59:01,070 --> 00:59:03,130
(panting)

863
00:59:16,020 --> 00:59:19,060
(breathing heavily)
What the fuck do you want?

864
00:59:19,970 --> 00:59:21,110
We're trying to locate
your father.

865
00:59:21,110 --> 00:59:23,900
You think my father
needs to see you?

866
00:59:23,900 --> 00:59:25,990
I'm afraid he has to.

867
00:59:29,000 --> 00:59:31,090
I hear your boy, Dr. Petey's
climbing the ladder.

868
00:59:32,050 --> 00:59:34,000
You keep it in the family, huh?

869
00:59:35,180 --> 00:59:37,140
Miss Detective Hewlett,

870
00:59:37,140 --> 00:59:40,190
has the good doctor here
explained the slash and burn
approach to life?

871
00:59:41,190 --> 00:59:43,160
-We can get a writ.
-(chuckles)

872
00:59:44,990 --> 00:59:47,950
You see, Petey and I were
accepted to the same med school,

873
00:59:47,950 --> 00:59:49,110
except I had to quit.

874
00:59:49,110 --> 00:59:51,100
Had a foot-the-bill problem
all of a sudden.

875
00:59:51,100 --> 00:59:52,990
Unemployment in the family.

876
00:59:54,180 --> 00:59:56,110
We can still get a writ.

877
01:00:00,930 --> 01:00:02,160
You wanna talk to my father?

878
01:00:03,990 --> 01:00:05,070
Come on.

879
01:00:05,070 --> 01:00:07,050
(dog barking in distance)

880
01:00:17,970 --> 01:00:19,070
(door closes)

881
01:00:20,120 --> 01:00:22,030
[Mort Jr.] Dad, somebody wants
to talk to you.

882
01:00:31,160 --> 01:00:33,190
-Mort?
-(gasps)

883
01:00:36,970 --> 01:00:39,960
One, two, three,

884
01:00:40,170 --> 01:00:43,130
four, five.

885
01:00:46,920 --> 01:00:49,970
One, two, three,

886
01:00:50,130 --> 01:00:52,940
four, five.

887
01:01:00,080 --> 01:01:02,090
You could've spared us this.

888
01:01:02,090 --> 01:01:04,910
What the fuck have you ever
spared him, huh?

889
01:01:04,910 --> 01:01:07,060
Besides, he's far enough along,
he doesn't care.

890
01:01:07,060 --> 01:01:08,150
(murmuring) One, two three...

891
01:01:08,150 --> 01:01:09,920
He's not confused about

892
01:01:09,920 --> 01:01:11,110
what he thinks
he remembers anymore.

893
01:01:11,110 --> 01:01:14,140
-Kinda makes him
a bad suspect, huh?
-One, two, three, four, five...

894
01:01:14,140 --> 01:01:16,050
So get the fuck out of here,
Dr. Palmer,

895
01:01:16,050 --> 01:01:17,920
before I hit you
with the lawsuit from hell.

896
01:01:17,920 --> 01:01:20,030
One, two, three, four, five.
One, two, three, four, five.

897
01:01:20,030 --> 01:01:21,090
One, two, three, four, five.

898
01:01:22,060 --> 01:01:23,950
-[Franz] One, two, three...
-How is your mother?

899
01:01:24,120 --> 01:01:25,910
What the fuck are you?

900
01:01:26,180 --> 01:01:28,110
-Hey! Hey! Hey!
-...three, four, five!

901
01:01:28,110 --> 01:01:30,130
-Hey! Hey!
-You want to take
another shot at her?

902
01:01:30,130 --> 01:01:32,020
She's not here!

903
01:01:32,020 --> 01:01:35,030
She couldn't take it anymore.
You're a fucking cancer!

904
01:01:35,030 --> 01:01:36,180
(speaking gibberish)

905
01:01:36,180 --> 01:01:38,190
-You're a fucking cancer.
-One, four, three, four...

906
01:01:38,190 --> 01:01:39,930
(panting)

907
01:01:39,930 --> 01:01:41,150
(Mort Jr. sobbing)
You fucking cancer.

908
01:01:44,050 --> 01:01:45,160
Why'd you have to say that?

909
01:01:45,160 --> 01:01:47,000
[Mort Jr.] You fucking cancer.

910
01:02:05,160 --> 01:02:07,900
It's exactly what he wanted.

911
01:02:07,900 --> 01:02:10,000
He wanted you to come there,
so you'd see that.

912
01:02:11,970 --> 01:02:12,990
(lighter clanks)

913
01:02:22,980 --> 01:02:25,040
We're wrong
ruling out a copycat.

914
01:02:25,900 --> 01:02:27,080
You said he was escalating.

915
01:02:27,080 --> 01:02:28,980
He's not escalating

916
01:02:28,980 --> 01:02:31,000
when he keeps his victim alive,

917
01:02:31,000 --> 01:02:33,190
when he leaves the body,
when he leaves his voice
on tape,

918
01:02:33,190 --> 01:02:36,050
and purposefully sends you
on a wild goose chase.

919
01:02:36,050 --> 01:02:38,000
That's a different MO.

920
01:02:39,040 --> 01:02:41,050
And I think it's an insider.

921
01:02:56,000 --> 01:02:57,190
I was in love with her.

922
01:02:59,190 --> 01:03:01,040
Isn't that amazing?

923
01:03:01,930 --> 01:03:03,100
Not so amazing.

924
01:03:05,160 --> 01:03:07,090
We were out of control.

925
01:03:09,110 --> 01:03:11,040
Tried to make it work.

926
01:03:13,110 --> 01:03:16,910
And then one day she just
packed her bags and left.

927
01:03:19,090 --> 01:03:20,940
I never saw her again.

928
01:03:23,110 --> 01:03:27,050
Kim and I separated and we,
eventually, we got a divorce.

929
01:03:29,000 --> 01:03:31,090
Then I quit and started writing.

930
01:03:34,020 --> 01:03:36,050
And in the process of it all...

931
01:03:37,990 --> 01:03:39,990
I lost my son, too.

932
01:03:43,130 --> 01:03:44,970
There's a difference.

933
01:03:48,050 --> 01:03:49,950
You can get yours back.

934
01:03:53,040 --> 01:03:54,120
(scoffs)

935
01:04:13,960 --> 01:04:15,990
-Joey!
-Joey!

936
01:04:15,990 --> 01:04:20,080
-Joey! Joey!
-Joey! Joey! Joey!

937
01:04:20,080 --> 01:04:22,040
-[Leslie] Okay, guys.
-[kids] Joey!

938
01:04:22,040 --> 01:04:24,130
-(Joey barking)
-(knocking on door)

939
01:04:25,140 --> 01:04:28,030
-[Leslie] Joey, hello!
What's up?
-[Kim] Hi, Joey.

940
01:04:28,030 --> 01:04:30,900
-[Mark] Hey, Joey.
-[Leslie] Everybody, take your
covers off, guys.

941
01:04:30,900 --> 01:04:34,020
Joey, what is this?
You wanna go out?

942
01:04:34,900 --> 01:04:36,030
(barking)

943
01:04:36,930 --> 01:04:38,130
Joey, what...

944
01:04:38,130 --> 01:04:40,010
(Joey growling)

945
01:04:51,080 --> 01:04:53,030
Oh, my God.

946
01:04:54,950 --> 01:04:56,090
(gasps)

947
01:05:13,040 --> 01:05:15,040
Kids, don't run.

948
01:05:19,170 --> 01:05:20,990
Leslie?

949
01:05:22,050 --> 01:05:24,190
Mommy, could I have some juice?

950
01:05:25,070 --> 01:05:26,940
Not now, honey.

951
01:05:29,070 --> 01:05:30,180
We've been robbed.

952
01:05:32,150 --> 01:05:33,940
We better call the police.

953
01:05:37,020 --> 01:05:39,070
(indistinct chatter
on police radio)

954
01:05:39,070 --> 01:05:41,050
-[Bill] How about this color?
-[Sharon] Dusted there...

955
01:05:41,050 --> 01:05:42,950
-[man] Thanks.
-[Sharon] Upstairs.

956
01:05:42,950 --> 01:05:44,180
I can't find Peter.

957
01:05:44,180 --> 01:05:47,100
I called his office, the gym,
all the usual places.

958
01:05:47,100 --> 01:05:50,000
Yeah, I know,
I called them, too.

959
01:05:50,000 --> 01:05:52,160
Daddy was gonna read me
this book tonight.

960
01:05:52,160 --> 01:05:53,970
Can you, grandpa?

961
01:05:53,970 --> 01:05:55,940
Sweetie, why don't I read it
for you upstairs?

962
01:05:55,940 --> 01:05:58,000
-Maybe another time.
-You want me to take your book?

963
01:06:01,140 --> 01:06:03,000
Is there anything missing?

964
01:06:03,000 --> 01:06:05,090
Um, no. Nothing.

965
01:06:07,130 --> 01:06:09,080
[Sharon] Maybe this
isn't a robbery.

966
01:06:09,080 --> 01:06:11,010
Maybe Peter just lost it.

967
01:06:12,970 --> 01:06:15,980
Okay, you can start cleaning up.
We're about done here.

968
01:06:16,970 --> 01:06:18,970
(dramatic music playing)

969
01:06:57,090 --> 01:06:59,070
You know he fits the category.

970
01:07:00,190 --> 01:07:02,180
What are you talking about?

971
01:07:02,180 --> 01:07:04,010
Peter.

972
01:07:04,190 --> 01:07:06,080
He's an insider.

973
01:07:06,080 --> 01:07:08,990
We said it had to be an insider.

974
01:07:08,990 --> 01:07:10,970
-You got to be kidding.
-Think about it.

975
01:07:10,970 --> 01:07:12,170
You're talking about my son.

976
01:07:12,170 --> 01:07:14,190
[Sharon] I'm talking
about a motive.

977
01:07:16,910 --> 01:07:18,920
(music continues)

978
01:07:35,090 --> 01:07:36,990
It's his copy.

979
01:07:47,180 --> 01:07:49,170
I've gotta take this to Cobb.

980
01:07:49,170 --> 01:07:50,990
It can't be.

981
01:07:53,150 --> 01:07:55,000
I'm sorry.

982
01:07:58,150 --> 01:08:01,000
-[Sharon] Bag, please.
-You're jumping to conclusions.

983
01:08:01,000 --> 01:08:02,150
There's not enough evidence.

984
01:08:02,150 --> 01:08:04,940
There's more
than enough evidence.

985
01:08:04,940 --> 01:08:05,990
I'm getting a warrant.

986
01:08:05,990 --> 01:08:07,120
What are you talking about?
For Peter?

987
01:08:08,090 --> 01:08:10,050
You're getting a warrant
for Peter?

988
01:08:10,050 --> 01:08:12,160
Are you crazy,
you son of a bitch?

989
01:08:12,160 --> 01:08:14,020
-You son of a bitch.
-Come on. Stop it right there.

990
01:08:14,020 --> 01:08:16,050
He's not here and you people
are making him out

991
01:08:16,050 --> 01:08:17,150
to be some kind of a criminal?

992
01:08:17,150 --> 01:08:19,070
I won't let you hurt him, Bill.

993
01:08:19,070 --> 01:08:20,140
You hear me?

994
01:08:20,140 --> 01:08:22,920
You cannot let anything
happen to him.

995
01:08:22,920 --> 01:08:24,100
Kim. Kim.

996
01:08:24,100 --> 01:08:28,160
-Look, nothing's gonna
happen to our son--
-(sobbing)

997
01:08:38,060 --> 01:08:39,900
Bill?

998
01:08:39,900 --> 01:08:41,100
You can't believe that.

999
01:08:42,090 --> 01:08:43,910
No.

1000
01:08:43,910 --> 01:08:45,930
But he fits the profile.

1001
01:08:45,930 --> 01:08:47,980
He does resent me.
Knows all about me.

1002
01:08:47,980 --> 01:08:49,010
That's a motive.

1003
01:08:49,010 --> 01:08:50,140
He doesn't resent you.

1004
01:08:50,140 --> 01:08:51,990
He wants to be like you.

1005
01:08:53,140 --> 01:08:56,900
You don't know what it's like
to have a father
you can't please.

1006
01:08:57,100 --> 01:08:59,090
He just wants your approval.

1007
01:09:02,060 --> 01:09:03,080
(scoffs)

1008
01:09:06,080 --> 01:09:07,130
Yeah.

1009
01:09:08,150 --> 01:09:10,110
There's something
I'm not getting.

1010
01:09:10,110 --> 01:09:12,020
What?

1011
01:09:13,930 --> 01:09:15,080
I have to check something.

1012
01:09:16,010 --> 01:09:17,970
I'll be back as soon as I can.

1013
01:09:34,150 --> 01:09:35,970
Perfect match.

1014
01:09:38,950 --> 01:09:42,170
I don't know.
He was here this morning,
but he seemed upset.

1015
01:09:42,170 --> 01:09:43,920
Trent.

1016
01:09:44,130 --> 01:09:45,930
You have a moment?

1017
01:09:45,930 --> 01:09:47,100
What's happening with Peter?

1018
01:09:47,100 --> 01:09:48,900
I need your help.

1019
01:09:48,900 --> 01:09:51,170
Well, the police,
they're all over his office.

1020
01:09:54,980 --> 01:09:56,140
I need to get into the morgue.

1021
01:09:57,160 --> 01:09:59,180
(intense music playing)

1022
01:10:09,150 --> 01:10:11,020
Where is he?

1023
01:10:11,150 --> 01:10:13,040
-Where the hell is he?
-Bill?

1024
01:10:13,040 --> 01:10:14,180
Bill. Bill.

1025
01:10:14,180 --> 01:10:16,130
-Time out. Time out.
-(panting)

1026
01:10:16,990 --> 01:10:18,960
-All right.
-You're with me?

1027
01:10:18,960 --> 01:10:20,960
Now, what are we looking for?

1028
01:10:20,960 --> 01:10:21,990
Um...

1029
01:10:22,930 --> 01:10:23,970
-Rocky.
-Rocky?

1030
01:10:23,970 --> 01:10:25,080
-Yeah.
-He's right here.

1031
01:10:31,920 --> 01:10:33,130
Let's take a look.

1032
01:10:39,150 --> 01:10:41,060
Who did the autopsy?

1033
01:10:41,960 --> 01:10:43,110
Well, nobody yet.

1034
01:10:45,950 --> 01:10:47,960
Where did these sutures
come from?

1035
01:10:48,170 --> 01:10:50,030
That's how he came in.

1036
01:10:53,160 --> 01:10:54,910
Rocky?

1037
01:10:57,150 --> 01:10:59,050
Talk to me, Rocky.

1038
01:11:03,000 --> 01:11:04,920
Tell me what I'm not seeing.

1039
01:11:12,940 --> 01:11:14,000
The woman.

1040
01:11:14,000 --> 01:11:16,050
The black woman
that Peter was working on,

1041
01:11:16,050 --> 01:11:17,170
where is she?

1042
01:11:17,170 --> 01:11:19,010
Right here.

1043
01:11:29,970 --> 01:11:32,040
Do you remember the fight
we had over this?

1044
01:11:33,050 --> 01:11:37,020
How he always does his stitches
the same way?

1045
01:11:37,020 --> 01:11:38,050
